<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97753898122824></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97753898122824><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=97753898122824>RE: why a stupid enchanter ?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=97753898122824#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 23rd 2:37 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The enchanter is rumored to be the hardest in the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have a enchanter, and I die constantly, mostly due to others not assisting when they should.  Both a cleric and an enchanter have to rely on the group.  HOWEVER, at high levels, the enchanter can be the more useful character to a group.  Played right, a group won't need a cleric for rezzes at all, but only for heals.  Lower levels, like under 46, are not easy.  Making some good friends is a requirement.  it's tough.  But the oparty NEEDS me, so it was worth it.  I can find any tank, casters love clarity, and while all I need is a cleric &lt;I die, did I say that?&gt; and I can clarity them!  So it's a lot of fun, if sometimes a bit slow...  but an enchanter is my main character for a reason.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
