	   <tr><td colspan=2>Enchanters are truely an amazing class. But it does take a certain kind of player to play one successfully. I may not be one of them lol, but I've pulled off some amazing things through my years (now 51 and not really playin anymore =P) If you know your spells, and form a strategy, you should do well. At low lvls, I'd say HH is a great place to get used to your CC abilities. <br><br>On the issue of solo'ing, I've solo'd all the way to 51 (not straight, but during them boring times with nothing to do hehe). From bards and dwarves, to spirocs and who know what all =p - if ya know how to charm, and how to use our weakling pet, you'll do just fine in the solo'ing department :)<br><br>well, anyways hehe<br>Good luck with your decision, and have fun (the most important thing:)<br><br>Anadaar Zh`alfirin<br>Teir`Dal Illusionist of the 51st Charm<br>Lost Legion<br>Emarr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
